{"verses":[{"id":6080,"verseNumber":1,"verseKey":"93:1","arabic":" وَٱلضُّحَىٰ","english":"By the morning sunlight,"},{"id":6081,"verseNumber":2,"verseKey":"93:2","arabic":"وَٱلَّيْلِ إِذَا سَجَىٰ","english":"and the night when it falls still!"},{"id":6082,"verseNumber":3,"verseKey":"93:3","arabic":"مَا وَدَّعَكَ رَبُّكَ وَمَا قَلَىٰ","english":"Your Lord ˹O Prophet˺ has not abandoned you, nor has He become hateful ˹of you˺."},{"id":6083,"verseNumber":4,"verseKey":"93:4","arabic":"وَلَلْـَٔاخِرَةُ خَيْرٌ لَّكَ مِنَ ٱلْأُولَىٰ","english":"And the next life is certainly far better for you than this one."},{"id":6084,"verseNumber":5,"verseKey":"93:5","arabic":"وَلَسَوْفَ يُعْطِيكَ رَبُّكَ فَتَرْضَىٰٓ","english":"And ˹surely˺ your Lord will give so much to you that you will be pleased."},{"id":6085,"verseNumber":6,"verseKey":"93:6","arabic":"أَلَمْ يَجِدْكَ يَتِيمًا فَـَٔاوَىٰ","english":"Did He not find you as an orphan then sheltered you?"},{"id":6086,"verseNumber":7,"verseKey":"93:7","arabic":"وَوَجَدَكَ ضَآلًّا فَهَدَىٰ","english":"Did He not find you unguided then guided you?"},{"id":6087,"verseNumber":8,"verseKey":"93:8","arabic":"وَوَجَدَكَ عَآئِلًا فَأَغْنَىٰ","english":"And did He not find you needy then satisfied your needs?"},{"id":6088,"verseNumber":9,"verseKey":"93:9","arabic":"فَأَمَّا ٱلْيَتِيمَ فَلَا تَقْهَرْ","english":"So do not oppress the orphan,"},{"id":6089,"verseNumber":10,"verseKey":"93:10","arabic":"وَأَمَّا ٱلسَّآئِلَ فَلَا تَنْهَرْ","english":"nor repulse the beggar.<sup foot_note=77625>1</sup>"},{"id":6090,"verseNumber":11,"verseKey":"93:11","arabic":"وَأَمَّا بِنِعْمَةِ رَبِّكَ فَحَدِّثْ","english":"And proclaim the blessings of your Lord."}]}
